10.body: We provide a custom error object that is utilized throughout the library.
10.title: API Error

11.body: We employ semantic HTTP codes to signify the type of error that occurred, enabling more precise error handling. If HTTP codes lack granularity, we offer a custom error code for more specific error handling scenarios. By default, HTTP codes are used.
11.breadcrumbs: API » Api Error » Error and HTTP Codes
11.title: Error and HTTP Codes

12.body: Custom error codes come into play when HTTP codes lack granularity. For instance, if you need to handle a particular error in a specific manner, custom error codes allow for such tailored handling. Custom error codes always consist of at least four digits to prevent conflicts with HTTP codes. We call these custom error codes Api Codes.
12.breadcrumbs: API » Api Error » Custom Error Codes
12.title: Custom Error Codes
